00:19:14,610 --> 00:19:16,580
He said that he would be leaving
by morning ship.

265
00:19:16,580 --> 00:19:18,100
Let' s go.

266
00:19:19,780 --> 00:19:22,550
-To America?
-By morning ship?

267
00:19:22,790 --> 00:19:25,810
He left so I wouldn't have to...

268
00:19:27,260 --> 00:19:31,590
So quickly.
Parting from him so quickly.

269
00:19:32,130 --> 00:19:34,300
No...!

270
00:19:34,300 --> 00:19:36,320
I don't want to part from you!

271
00:19:37,700 --> 00:19:39,430
No!

272
00:20:50,970 --> 00:20:52,910
I turned up late.

273
00:21:06,560 --> 00:21:09,680
I couldn't see him.

274
00:21:16,270 --> 00:21:19,440
Terry I...

275
00:21:19,440 --> 00:21:22,340
I love you.

276
00:21:22,670 --> 00:21:26,610
Candy! wherever I might end up
I' ll be praying for your happiness.

277
00:21:26,610 --> 00:21:31,710
Terry!

278
00:21:42,090 --> 00:21:43,430
Just my imagination.

279
00:21:43,430 --> 00:21:47,660
I must be imagining it
since we first met on such a ship.

280
00:21:47,660 --> 00:21:49,800
The shore is already far...

281
00:21:49,800 --> 00:21:54,130
Candy, be happy.
But someday... for sure.

282
00:22:07,520 --> 00:22:12,110
Terry, what should I do?
What should I do?

283
00:22:12,420 --> 00:22:16,230
Did you think that staying here
would've brought me happiness?

284
00:22:16,230 --> 00:22:21,090
Terry!

285
00:22:22,970 --> 00:22:25,870
While this painful parting
was taking place.

286
00:22:25,870 --> 00:22:32,470
Candy would have herself
expelled from school.

